# Config Generation

## Source of truth

Upstream: `https://github.com/ceph/ceph` → `src/common/options/*.yaml.in`

## Regenerate workflow

```bash
pip install -r scripts/requirements.txt
python3 scripts/generate-config.py --ref main   # or reef, squid, …
python3 scripts/split-index.py                  # only if readme.md edited manually
python3 scripts/sync-docs-index.py              # if REFERENCE.md changed
```

## File layout (do not change without updating generate-config.py)

- `config/<subsystem>/*.md` — option tables grouped by name prefix
- `config/readme.md` — master index (auto-generated)
- `config/<subsystem>/INDEX.md` — split index (via split-index.py)
- `VERSION` — records upstream ref and timestamp

## Table format

Keep 16-column table schema used by `generate-config.py` and `lookup-config.sh`.

## Adding a new upstream subsystem

1. Add to `SUBSYSTEMS` in `generate-config.py` and `split-index.py`
2. Add row to `config/OVERVIEW.md` and `mkdocs.yml` nav
3. Regenerate
